In general, indoor light is measured as photometric illuminance L (lx), which is typically in the range of 100–1000 lx. Theoretically, L and Pin of an arbitrary light source can be calculated by integrating the spectral irradiance F(λ) (mW cm−2 nm−1) using Eqs. 4 and 5:4Pin=∫F(λ)dλ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
